Identify the gluteus medius and minimus. Follow the superior gluteal nerve into the plane between these two muscles, running toward the tensor fascia lata. The superior gluteal nerve innervates these three muscles. What actions is it responsible for? Think then click     !
The inferior gluteal nerve innervates the gluteus maximus. What movements is it responsible for? Think then click     !
Gluteus maximus: extension and lateral rotation of the hip.
Gluteus medius and minimus: abduction and medial rotation of the hip . TFL: medial rotation and flexion of the hip.
It is a lateral rotator of the hip joint.
